stimulus:
Welcome to the study. You will first complete a short volume calibration and headphone check.

Please make sure you are in a quiet listening environment, that you are wearing headphones, and that your computer's volume is turned on.

The volume calibration will be first.

You will hear a thirty-second noise. Please adjust your computer's volume so that this noise is being presented at a comfortable level.

You will now complete a short headphone check.

On each trial, you will hear three tones. One of these tones will be quieter than the others. Your task is to identify whether the quiet tone occured first, second, or third.

There are six trials in total.
The volume calibration and headphone check are now complete.

Thank you for your answers.

You will now listen to similar sounds. The main difference is that the sounds will be longer and will make up complete sentences.

Please listen carefully to each sentence. After each sentence, you will be asked to type back what you heard to the best of your ability. After you provide your response, you will be given feedback about the correct answer.

There are 10 sentences in total.
